"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089464","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-20","<p>76 Chagossians have participated in five Heritage Visits to date which have been funded by the Support Package. This breaks down by country:</p><p> </p><p>Seychelles: 7<br>Mauritius: 18<br>UK: 51<br>Other countries: 0</p><p> </p><p>There have been 156 initial expressions of interest who have not participated in a Heritage Visit. Not all went onto complete questionnaires, and of those who did, not all met the requirements to participate in a Heritage Visit.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-03-20T16:02:30.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089464/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089464/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089464/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-15","Ilois: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 14 March 2019 to Question 230807 on Ilois Finance, how many visits £312,899.37 has financed, and how many Chagossians have to date (a) expressed interest but not yet participated and (b) participated in those visits from (i) Seychelles, (ii) Mauritius, (iii) the UK and (iv) other countries.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","233007"
