specialists, teaching unions, charities and faith groups. The Department analysed the responses to the consultation and have since published the Government response and updated the draft statutory guidance.</p><p>The key decisions on these subjects have also been informed by a thorough engagement process. The public call for evidence received over 23,000 responses from parents, young people and schools, and the Department engaged with 90 organisations representing a broad range of views. These stakeholders can be found in the Government response to the Call for Evidence at: <a href="https://consult.education.gov.uk/pshe/relationships-education-rse-health-education/supporting_documents/180718%20Consultation_call%20for%20evidence%20response_policy%20statement.pdf" target="_blank">https://consult.education.gov.uk/pshe/relationships-education-rse-health-education/supporting_documents/180718%20Consultation_call%20for%20evidence%20response_policy%20statement.pdf</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","232970 ; 232971","2019-03-25T15:08:02.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089491/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089491/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089491/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-15","Personal, Social, Health and Economic Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, who his Department consulted before drawing up the draft statutory guidance on Relationship's Education and Relationships and Sex Education for governing bodies, proprietors, head teachers, principals, senior leadership teams, teachers; what research was evaluated; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","232972"
