"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089493","Treasury","true","2019-03-20","<p>Currently, no commemorative coins to mark the UK’s departure from the <del class="ministerial">UK</del> <ins class="ministerial">EU </ins>have been minted. However, as is standard procedure at The Royal Mint, a small number of trial coins have been produced. The production of trial coins does not incur any cost to the taxpayer.<ins class="ministerial"> The commemorative 50 pence coin to mark the UK leaving the European Union will be made available following our departure.</ins></p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-03-20T17:00:04.883Z","2019-03-27T11:27:19.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089493/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089493/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089493/answer","Newark","Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1089493/answer/previousversion/109098","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-03-15","Coinage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the commemorative 50 pence coin issued to mark the UK's departure from the EU has been minted.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","233006"
